arning%20To%20West%3A%20Beware%20Of%20Bigger%20Governments%20You%20Wish%20For%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20'New%20York%20Times'-listed%20bestselling%20author%20and%20head%20of%20the%20Rockefeller%20Capital%20Management's%20international%20business%2C%20Ruchir%20Sharma%2C%20will%20be%20out%20with%20his%20new%20book%2C%20'What%20Went%20Wrong%20With%20Capitalism'%2C%20on%20June%2016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20be%20the%20'Financial%20Times'%20columnist's%20fifth%20book%20after%20'The%2010%20Rules%20of%20Successful%20Nations'%2C%20published%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20the%20announcement%2C%20the%20publishing%20house%2C%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20UK%2C%20said%20that%20in%20the%20upcoming%20book%2C%20Sharma%20%26quot%3Brewrites%20the%20standard%20histories%2C%20which%20trace%20today's%20popular%20anger%20to%20the%20anti-government%20rebellion%20that%20began%20under%20Margaret%20Thatcher%20and%20Ronald%20Reagan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20book%20that%20promises%20to%20help%20us%20understand%20the%20growing%20popular%20anger%20in%20the%20capitalist%20world%20(at%20the%20moment%20expressing%20itself%20in%20the%20protests%20raging%20across%20US%20campuses)%2C%20its%20fundamental%20argument%2C%20according%20to%20the%20press%20statement%20from%20the%20publisher%2C%20can%20be%20summed%20up%20in%20this%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BFour%20decades%20of%20downsizing%20government%20--%20cutting%20taxes%2C%20spending%2C%20and%20regulations%20--%20left%20the%20financial%20markets%20free%20to%20run%20wild%2C%20fuelling%20inequality%2C%20slowing%20growth%20--%20and%20alienating%20much%20of%20the%20population.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharma%2C%20a%20Shri%20Ram%20College%20of%20Commerce%20alumnus%2C%20first%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20breadth%20of%20his%20vision%20with%20his%20debut%20book%2C%20Breakout%20Nations%20(2012)%2C%20which%20made%20the%20journal%20'Foreign%20Policy'%20rank%20him%20as%20one%20of%20the%20top%20global%20thinkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20upcoming%20book%2C%20Sharma%2C%20according%20to%20the%20publisher's%20press%20statement%2C%20%26quot%3Bexposes%20the%20story%20of%20a%20shrinking%20government%20as%20a%20myth%26quot%3B.%20The%20statement%20adds%3A%20%26quot%3BWith%20a%20historical%20and%20global%20sweep%2C%20%5BSharma%5D%20shows%20that%20the%20government%20has%20expanded%20steadily%20as%20a%20regulator%2C%20borrower%2C%20spender%2C%20and%20micro-manager%20of%20the%20business%20cycle%20for%20a%20century.%20Working%20with%20central%20banks%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20last%20two%20decades%2C%20governments%20created%20a%20culture%20of%20easy%20money%20and%20bailouts%20that%20is%20making%20the%20rich%20richer%2C%20and%20big%20companies%20bigger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20observation%20that%20may%20explain%20the%20appeal%20of%20the%20left-of-centre%20US%20Senator%20Bernie%20Sanders%20among%20young%20Americans%2C%20Sharma%20says%20%26quot%3Bprogressive%20youth%20are%20partly%20right%20that%20capitalism%20has%20morphed%20into%20'socialism%20for%20the%20very%20rich'.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharma%20notes%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20broader%20issue%2C%20however%2C%20is%20socialised%20risk%20for%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20middle%20class%20and%20the%20rich%3B%20the%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20guarantee%20that%20no%20one%20ever%20suffers%20economic%20pain%20by%20borrowing%20heavily%20to%20prevent%20recessions%2C%20extend%20recoveries%2C%20and%20generate%20endless%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20result%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20rapidly%20rising%20debt%20and%20declining%20competition%20--%20exactly%20the%20environment%20in%20which%20oligopolies%20and%20billionaires%20do%20best.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESays%20the%20book's%20blurb%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20rare%20capitalist%20critique%20of%20capitalism%20offers%20a%20timely%20warning.%20To%20a%20surprising%20degree%2C%20politicians%20on%20both%20the%20right%20and%20left%20now%20assume%20that%20popular%20anger%20with%20capitalism%20arose%20in%20a%20period%20of%20shrinking%20government%2C%20and%20so%20offer%20answers%20that%20involve%20more%20government%20--%20more%20spending%2C%20or%20regulation%2C%20or%20walls%20and%20barriers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20blurb%20goes%20on%20to%20note%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20their%20historical%20assumptions%20are%20incorrect%2C%20their%20proposed%20fixes%20are%20likely%20to%20double%20down%20on%20what%20went%20wrong%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20There%20is%20no%20returning%20to%20the%2019th%20century%20when%20the%20government%20did%20little%20more%20than%20deliver%20mail%2C%20but%20the%20balance%20has%20shifted%20too%20far%20towards%20state%20control%2C%20leaving%20too%20little%20room%20for%20economic%20competition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20whether%20your%20politics%20are%20progressive%20or%20conservative%2C%20Sharma%20argues%2C%20the%20answer%20has%20to%20be%20less%20government%20and%20more%20cautious%20central%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommenting%20on%20his%20%26quot%3Bmost%20ambitious%20book%20yet%26quot%3B%2C%20Sharma%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20book%20is%20a%20pandemic%20baby%2C%20conceived%20in%20that%20dark%20period%20when%20governments%20were%20both%20locking%20down%20businesses%20and%20spending%20trillions%20to%20support%20people%20shut%20in%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20many%20saw%20this%20crisis%20as%20entirely%20novel%2C%20what%20I%20saw%20was%20the%20logical%20culmination%20of%20all%20that%20has%20gone%20wrong%20with%20capitalism%2C%20namely%2C%20decades%20of%20increasingly%20interventionist%20government%2C%20narrowing%20the%20scope%20of%20individual%20freedom%20and%20initiative%20and%20economic%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714757940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%